Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_ml_design(25.10)                                  write_ml_design(25.10)

Name
       write_ml_design  -  Writes  design-related  data for JedAI to csv files
       with specified prefix

Syntax
       write_ml_design

       [-help]

       [-no_power]

       [-objects <object_list>]

       -prefix <string>

       [-verbose]

       [-views <view_list>]

       Writes design-related data for JedAI to csv files with  specified  pre-
       fix.  It  includes data that is design specific and relates to logical,
       physical, and timing type objects.

       Before running write_ml_design, the following two  commands  should  be
       run:

              * report_timing

              * write_global_slack_report -include_ports

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each write_ml_design parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man write_ml_design.

       -no_power
              Specifies that power attributes should not be dumped.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -objects <object_list>
              Specifies the list of db object(s) to be dumped, which could in-
              clude one or more of the following values:

              analysis_view arc base_cell base_pin blockage cell_density clock
              congestion

              constraint_mode delay_corner design gcell_grid hinst  hnet  hpin
              hport inst

              layer  marker net netlist opcond option p2p partition patch_wire
              pg_base_pin

              pg_pin  pin  pin_shape  port  rc_corner  route_rule   row   site
              skew_group special_net

              timing_condition track_pattern unit_parasitic via_def

              Use curly braces to enclose multiple values.

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix for the output files.

              Data_type: string, required

       -verbose
              Displays a more detailed message.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -views <view_list>
              Dumps the data for the specified analysis view(s).

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

Example
              * The  following command writes the attributes of all design ob-
                jects to csv files with the specified prefix:

                write_ml_design -prefix out/

Related Information
              * init_ml

              * report_timing

              * write_global_slack_report

              * write_ml_library

              * write_ml_timing_graph

              * write_ml_timing_path

